&gt; And, to answer a reference to money: My experience with Chris Moon didn&#39;t cost a cent.  In fact, the box spoke to me from across a large room -- I&#39;d guess about 20 or 30 feet away and from a platform about 10 feet above me -- in a distinctive voice and speech pattern that I recognized immediately.  
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;d asked a rhetorical question. The box answered. That rattled me, big time.  After that, I stuck close to the box.  I wanted to hear more.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; However, at no time did this involve payment of any kind.  In fact, innate skeptic that I am (having been badly burned by one regrettable association), I watched Chris and Dina closely during the weekend.  I saw zero hustling or salesmanship. They never asked me for money, and have never asked me to talk about my experiences with the box.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; My interest in the boxes and this list are unabashedly self-serving:  I want to understand why some devices work better than others, why some of us hear them more clearly than others, who the voices really are (if they&#39;re not who they seem to be), and the significance of what they&#39;re saying.  I want to hear more.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I don&#39;t have the expertise to build a box, and I can&#39;t afford to hire someone to build one for me, right now.  So, I&#39;m on this list, listening vicariously to others&#39; experiences and recordings.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;m grateful for those who share their insights, experiences, thoughts on how we can understand this stuff better, and the recordings of voices that keep talking & talking.
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Thanks again, Frank!
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Relieved,
&gt; 
&gt; Fiona
